Logics.

We have:
int[] arr - sorted array
int left - starting index of array
int right - last index of array
mid - middle of array, where mid = left + (right - left) / 2
X - value to find

Step 1.
Calculate the middle

Step 2.
Check if middle is a X
    if - yes, return middle

Step 3.
Check if middle > than X
    if yes, cut array in half. mid - 1 , becomes new right and function calls itself
    if no, cut array in half, mid +1, becomes new left function calls itself

Step 4.
    if found nothing return -1

